@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "RA Protein Knowledge Platform";
}

@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/page2.css" asp-append-version="true" />
}

@section Menu {
    <li class="nav-item">
        <a class="nav-link" href="#workflow">Method</a>
    </li>
    <li class="nav-item">
        <a class="nav-link" href="#modules">Knowledge Framework</a>
    </li>
    <li class="nav-item">
        <a class="nav-link" href="/KnowledgeBase">Database</a>
    </li>
    <li class="nav-item">
        <a class="nav-link" href="/Docking">Docking</a>
    </li>
}

<div class="ra-platform-page">
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="container-custom hero-grid">
            <div class="hero-copy">
                <div class="eyebrow">Curated • Mechanism-aware • Docking-ready</div>

                <h1>
                    A curated RA protein knowledge platform for mechanism interpretation and docking-guided exploration
                </h1>

                <p class="lead">
                    From broad inflammatory candidates to a refined 64-protein knowledge base, this platform transforms biological complexity into a structured, disease-aware, and application-ready resource for rheumatoid arthritis research.
                </p>

                <p class="hero-cn">
                    该平台并非简单收集蛋白，而是通过三阶段筛选流程，将炎症候选、RA核心机制与药理相关节点整合为一个可解释、可追溯、可用于对接分析的知识系统。
                </p>

                <div class="hero-tags">
                    <span class="hero-tag">Mechanism-aware</span>
                    <span class="hero-tag">Disease-oriented</span>
                    <span class="hero-tag">Structured knowledge</span>
                    <span class="hero-tag">Docking-connected</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="hero-panel">
                <div class="panel-title">Curation overview</div>

                <div class="flow-mini">
                    <div class="flow-item">
                        <span class="flow-step">Version 1</span>
                        <h4>Broad inflammatory candidate pool</h4>
                        <p>
                            Wide coverage of inflammatory and immune-related molecules to preserve pathway completeness and avoid premature information loss.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flow-item">
                        <span class="flow-step">Version 2</span>
                        <h4>RA Core / RA Drug branching</h4>
                        <p>
                            Mechanistic separation into disease-specific pathology and pharmacologically interpretable inflammatory pathways.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flow-item">
                        <span class="flow-step">Final</span>
                        <h4>Integrated 64-protein knowledge base</h4>
                        <p>
                            A compact final panel balancing disease mechanism, interpretability, and downstream docking utility.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="workflow" class="section workflow">
        <div class="container-custom">
            <div class="section-head">
                <span class="kicker">Curation workflow</span>
                <h2>How the knowledge base was built</h2>
                <p>
                    A three-stage workflow was used to distinguish broad inflammatory signals, RA-specific disease mechanisms, and application-ready targets. The goal was not maximum inclusion, but meaningful biological structure.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="workflow-grid">
                <div class="workflow-card">
                    <div class="num">1</div>
                    <h3>Version 1 — Broad candidate pool</h3>
                    <p>
                        A wide set of inflammatory and immune-related molecules was retained to capture upstream activation, signaling amplification, immune participation, and feedback regulation.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="workflow-card">
                    <div class="num">2</div>
                    <h3>Version 2 — Mechanistic branching</h3>
                    <p>
                        The collection was separated into two directions: <strong>RA Core</strong> for disease pathology and <strong>RA Drug</strong> for pharmacologically interpretable inflammatory pathways.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="workflow-card">
                    <div class="num">3</div>
                    <h3>Final — Integrated 64-protein panel</h3>
                    <p>
                        The final set recombines disease-core proteins with key drug-relevant nodes, producing a compact and explainable RA protein framework for docking and analysis.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="workflow-note">
                <strong>Key idea:</strong> this platform is not built by simply collecting proteins. It is built by preserving what is biologically informative, disease-relevant, and practically useful.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="modules" class="section modules">
        <div class="container-custom">
            <div class="section-head">
                <span class="kicker">Knowledge framework</span>
                <h2>The 64-protein RA knowledge framework</h2>
                <p>
                    The final collection is organized by biological function so users can understand RA as a structured disease system rather than a flat list of molecular names.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="module-grid">
                <div class="module-card">
                    <div class="module-chip chip-blue">Module 01</div>
                    <h3>Inflammatory signaling</h3>
                    <p>
                        Core inflammatory drivers that connect immune activation to downstream cytokine release, pathway amplification, and therapeutic interpretation.
                    </p>
                    <div class="protein-list">
                        <span class="protein-tag">TNFA</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">IL6</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">JAK1</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">JAK2</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">TYK2</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">NFKB1</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">TF65</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">TLR7</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">CASP1</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card">
                    <div class="module-chip chip-green">Module 02</div>
                    <h3>Synovial invasion &amp; matrix degradation</h3>
                    <p>
                        Proteins associated with synovial aggressiveness, extracellular matrix breakdown, angiogenesis, and persistent tissue damage in RA.
                    </p>
                    <div class="protein-list">
                        <span class="protein-tag">MMP2</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">MMP8</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">MMP9</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">FAK1</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">RHOA</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">HGF</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">MET</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">VGFR2</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card">
                    <div class="module-chip chip-purple">Module 03</div>
                    <h3>Autoimmune regulation</h3>
                    <p>
                        Immune-regulatory and RA-associated molecules linked to adaptive immunity, autoimmune susceptibility, and sustained pathogenic signaling.
                    </p>
                    <div class="protein-list">
                        <span class="protein-tag">IL2</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">IL2RB</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">DRB1</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">PADI4</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">PTN22</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">SYK</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">HCK</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">SRC</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card">
                    <div class="module-chip chip-red">Module 04</div>
                    <h3>Regulatory / background support</h3>
                    <p>
                        Contextual and modulatory proteins that support network completeness, biological interpretation, and broader pathway context.
                    </p>
                    <div class="protein-list">
                        <span class="protein-tag">AHR</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">ABCG2</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">PPARA</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">PPARG</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">PPIA</span>
                        <span class="protein-tag">XCT</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="modules-summary">
                The 64-protein collection is designed as a disease-aware framework rather than a flat molecular inventory.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section value">
        <div class="container-custom">
            <div class="section-head">
                <span class="kicker">Platform value</span>
                <h2>Why this platform matters</h2>
                <p>
                    The purpose of this platform is to turn protein collection into explainable disease knowledge, and connect that knowledge to docking and downstream analysis.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="value-grid">
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Curated biological relevance</h3>
                    <p>
                        Proteins are retained based on disease significance, mechanistic contribution, and interpretability rather than simple inclusion.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Explainable RA structure</h3>
                    <p>
                        The platform preserves not only inflammatory markers, but also the pathological architecture of RA, including invasion, degradation, angiogenesis, and autoimmune regulation.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Application-ready design</h3>
                    <p>
                        The final protein panel is structured for direct integration with SMILES-based docking, result interpretation, and table-driven analysis workflows.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="value-quote">
                We do not simply collect proteins. We organize rheumatoid arthritis into a searchable, interpretable, docking-connected knowledge system.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>